Michael Antoine Crooms (born October 5, 1970), better known by his stage name Mr. Collipark (and also known as DJ Smurf), is an American hip hop producer and the president of his own Atlanta-based record label, Collipark Music, which was started in 1999.
In 2007, Mr. Collipark won BMI's "Songwriter of the Year" award.
